Welcome back Frank,

I have a question for you. You have given boxes all men here in the group
except one man has any woman been given the opportunity to have a box? I
have requested one for a  long time now and even offered to pay you.

But if you just send me the schematics I will build it, I am studying
electronics now and here in Mexico the random would be a good thing I
believe. Because even though  there&#39;s no English speaking stations near me
all I get is English J



Laura



From: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com [mailto:EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com] On Behalf Of
Frank Sumption
Sent: Saturday, February 02, 2008 9:17 PM
To: evp-itc@yahoogroups.com
Subject: RE: [EVP-ITC] Yeah--it works.




 There is a lack of the background hiss, and white noise of the random tuned
systems.

 The sweep circuit is simple, and using pre-made tuners a real time saver,
provided a source for the older tuners can be found. I used to get them from
junk yards, but the old radios are getting harder to find. They have the
advantage of all the RF components matching the chip.

 Frank-S

